\section{Implementation Details}

\subsection{State Serialization}

The core challenge is maintaining state across stateless HTTP requests:

\begin{lstlisting}[language=Python, style=mystyle]
def _get_state(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:
    """Serialize current environment state."""
    return {
        "task_id": self.task_id,
        "current_step": self.current_step,
        "max_steps": self.max_steps,
        "experiments": [serialize_experiment(e) for e in self.experiments],
        "episode_history": self.episode_history,
        "done": self.done,
        "total_reward": self.total_reward,
    }

def step(self, action, serialized_state=None, **kwargs):
    """Restore state from action if provided."""
    if serialized_state:
        self._restore_state(serialized_state)
    # ... process action
    return MLTriageObservation(
        # ...,
        serialized_state=self._get_state()
    )
\end{lstlisting}

This pattern ensures each request carries the complete game state.

