\subsection{Environment Factory}

The environment is instantiated via a factory function:

\begin{lstlisting}[language=Python, style=mystyle]
from openenv_core import create_app

def create_env():
    return MLTriageEnvironment()

app = create_app(
    create_env,
    MLTriageAction,
    MLTriageObservation,
    env_name="ml-experiment-triage"
)
\end{lstlisting}

This allows OpenEnv to create fresh instances for each request.

