\section{Inference Pipeline}

The inference script demonstrates an AI agent playing the game:

\begin{figure}[h]
\centering
\begin{tikzpicture}[
    node distance=1.2cm,
    step/.style={rectangle, draw, rounded corners, minimum width=2.5cm, minimum height=0.8cm, align=center},
    arrow/.style={thick,->,>=stealth}
]

\node[step, fill=blue!20] (s1) at (0,0) {1. Reset};
\node[step, fill=green!20] (s2) at (2,0) {2. Observe};
\node[step, fill=yellow!20] (s3) at (4,0) {3. LLM Action};
\node[step, fill=orange!20] (s4) at (6,0) {4. Execute};
\node[step, fill=red!20] (s5) at (8,0) {5. Reward};

\draw[arrow] (s1) -- (s2);
\draw[arrow] (s2) -- (s3);
\draw[arrow] (s3) -- (s4);
\draw[arrow] (s4) -- (s5);

\end{tikzpicture}
\end{figure}

The workflow:
\begin{enumerate}
	\item \textbf{Reset}: Initialize environment with task
	\item \textbf{Observation}: Format experiments as text
	\item \textbf{Action}: Ask LLM (GPT-4) what to do
	\item \textbf{Step}: Execute action, get reward
	\item \textbf{Repeat}: Until done or max steps
\end{enumerate}

\begin{lstlisting}[language=Python, style=mystyle]
# Get observation
obs = response.json()['observation']
state = obs.get('serialized_state', {})

# Format for LLM
obs_text = f"Task: {obs['task_description']}\n"
obs_text += "Experiments:\n"
for e in obs['experiments']:
    obs_text += f"  {e['exp_id']}: val_acc={e['val_acc']}\n"

# Get action from LLM
action = get_action(obs_text, history)

# Pass state back
action['serialized_state'] = state
response = requests.post('/step', json={'action': action})
\end{lstlisting}

The LLM is prompted to respond with valid JSON only, ensuring clean parsing.

